            <h1 class="text-primary">B. Tyler Blair</h1>
            <h3>Law Student</h3>
            <p>As a third year student at Suffolk Law School, my legal work so far includes
              exposure to legislation, litigation, and transactions.&nbsp;
              <br>
              <br>Prior to law school, I spent four years working in higher education as
              an advisor to undergraduates. During this time I advised student groups
              on issues of organizational management, including issues of mission and
              purpose, goal setting, budgeting, officer transitions, effective meeting
              facilitation, marketing and recruitment, diversity and inclusion, conflict
              resolution, and member accountability. I also advised individual student
              leaders on issues of personal development and leading with integrity. Advising
              took the form of workshops, conferences, classes, service-learning projects
              and one-on-one counseling.
              <br>
              <br>During that time, I developed a strong interest in
              <b>technology</b>and the role modern tools can play in both education, and
              in operational management. In higher education, I helped a non profit build
              and execute a comprehensive e-learning platform. And most recently, I participated
              in a course at law school focused around centering how to use technology
              to advance the legal profession. Take a look below at some of my work product
              that is a result of that course.
              <br>
              <br>
            </p>
